\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\ulnone\fs28 6. Discuss the role of Remote Desktop Services (RDS) in Windows Server 2016 or 2019 and how to configure it?\par
\b0 Ans. Remote Desktop Services (RDS) in Windows Server 2016/2019 allows users to remotely connect to a server and run applications, desktops, or full virtual environments as if they were local.\par
\b Key Roles of RDS\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Centralized Application Hosting \b0\endash  Run apps on the server, users access them remotely.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b Remote Desktop Access \b0\endash  Users connect to a virtual desktop from anywhere.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b Cost-Effective \b0\endash  Reduces need for high-performance hardware on client machines.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b Security & Control \b0\endash  IT admins can manage apps, updates, and policies centrally.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b Supports BYOD (Bring Your Own Device) \b0\endash  Users can connect from PCs, thin clients, or mobile devices.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b RDS Components\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj RD Session Host (RDSH): \b0 Hosts Windows-based applications or full desktops for remote users.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b RD Connection Broker: \b0 Manages user sessions, load balancing, and reconnects users to existing sessions.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b RD Web Access: \b0 Provides access to applications or desktops through a web portal.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b RD Gateway: \b0 Enables secure remote connections over the internet using HTTPS.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}\b RD Licensing: \b0 Manages Remote Desktop CALs (Client Access Licenses).\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b How to Configure RDS in Windows Server 2016/2019\b0\par
\b Step 1: Install Remote Desktop Services Role\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Open Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f0  Manage \f2\u8594?\f0  Add Roles and Features.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Select Role-based or feature-based installation.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Choose the target server.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}From the roles list, select Remote Desktop Services \f2\u8594?\f0  Add features.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Select RDS role services you want (e.g., RD Session Host, RD Licensing, RD Web Access).\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Complete installation.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Step 2: Configure RD Session Host\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj In Server Manager, go to Remote Desktop Services.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Deploy Session-based Desktop Deployment (for desktops) or Virtual machine-based deployment (for VDI).\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Assign roles to servers (if you have multiple servers, e.g., one for RD Connection Broker, one for Session Host).\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Step 3: Configure Licensing\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj Open Server Manager \f2\u8594?\f0  Remote Desktop Services \f2\u8594?\f0  Overview.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Click on RD Licensing \f2\u8594?\f0  Add your license server.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Activate the license server via RD Licensing Manager.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Install CALs (User CAL or Device CAL, depending on your licensing model).\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Step 4: Configure RD Gateway (Optional \f2\endash\f0  for internet access)\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b0 Install RD Gateway role service.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Configure certificates for secure HTTPS connections.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Allow users to connect securely over the internet.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj\b Step 5: Publish Applications or Desktops\b0\par

\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\qj In Server Manager, go to Remote Desktop Services \f2\u8594?\f0  Collections.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Create a new Session Collection.\par
{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}Add apps or full desktop sessions that users can access.\par

